[1] Cases in various countries:
Americas
Mexico and Central America
---
Mexico:
- national. 13 Feb 2016. (reported) in January 2016, 50 cases; states affected -- Chiapas 25 cases, Oaxaca 21 cases, remaining cases in Guerrero, Sinaloa, Veracruz and Yucatan.
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/mexico-reports-50-zika-cases-in-january-most-in-chiapas-and-oaxaca-19257/

- Guadalajara. 22 Jan 2016. (conf.) 1 case, apparently locally acquired.
http://www.informador.com.mx/jalisco/2016/639998/6/registran-primer-caso-de-virus-zika-en-jalisco.htm [in Spanish]

El Salvador. 5 Feb 2016. (reported) government distributing mosquito larvae-eating fish as a Zika virus mosquito vector control measure.
http://www.latinoshealth.com/articles/18276/20160205/zika-virus-update-el-salvador-finds-best-way-to-fight-infection-see-how-they-do-it-here.htm#disqus_thread

Honduras. 9 Feb 2016. (registered) 4785 cases with no cases of birth defects; Guillain-Barre syndrome (GBS) 35 cases.
http://news.co.cr/honduras-registers-35-cases-of-rare-guillain-barre-nerve-disorder-linked-to-zika/44595/

[There is no indication of whether the 35 GBS cases are associated with Zika virus infections or whether this number is greater than that historically for the same period of time. - Mod.TY]

