Puerto Rico. 12 Feb 2016. (conf) as of 30 Jan 2016, 30 cases; one case a woman in the 1st trimester of pregnancy, another a patient hospitalized for Guillain-Barre syndrome.
https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/to-your-health/wp/2016/02/12/cdc-puerto-rico-seeing-mounting-cases-of-zika-virus-infection/

Barbados. 9 Feb 2016. (conf) 7 cases of whom 3 are pregnant.
http://www.caribbean360.com/news/three-pregnant-women-test-positive-for-zika-in-barbados

